cs.NI, cs.COMM, cs.AR, cs.CR, cs.IT 

This paper discusses the performance and buffering requirements of TCP/IP over ATM networks, which are primarily used for communication and networking. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also discusses congestion control and switch algorithms, which are related to communication protocols, making cs.COMM (Communications) another likely category. The paper also mentions the dynamics and performance of the TCP/IP protocol, which falls under the category of cs.AR (Architecture and Real-Time Systems). Additionally, the paper discusses the buffering requirements of ATM switches and edge devices, which are related to computer networks and systems, making cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) and cs.IT (Information Theory) possible categories as well.
